  "text": "A major focus area for disease-modifying therapeutic development in HD is to lower the levels of mHTT in the cell to alleviate neuropathology [CITATION_1] . The monogenic inheritance of HD does favour therapeutic approaches which reduce expression of the mHTT allele by targeting DNA and RNA with gene silencing technologies [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Alternative efforts have focussed on lowering mHTT by increasing the degradation of mHTT through increased flux of UPS and autophagic pathways. The therapies discussed below are summarized in Table 1 .",
